 {"id":"wa-4vx.9.4","title":"Hot reload support for safe settings (watcher poll interval, retention, log level)","description":"# Task: Hot reload config (safe subset)

## Goal
Allow `wa watch --reload-config` (or SIGHUP) to reload non-destructive settings.

## Rules
Only reload settings that cannot corrupt state:
- poll intervals
- retention
- log level
- pattern pack enablement

Do NOT hot reload:
- DB path
- vendoring mode
- anything that would require reinitialization

## Testing
- Integration tests:
  - change poll interval in config and verify watcher applies without restart
  - attempt to change forbidden fields (DB path) and verify watcher refuses / requires restart
  - reload does not lose locks or corrupt writer state

## Acceptance Criteria
- Poll interval changes apply without restart.
- Forbidden settings are rejected with an actionable message.
